attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Ce commerce a toujours vendu du foie gras.
Le propriétaire actuel est là depuis une vingtaine d'années.
Le restaurant existe depuis une dizaine d'années basé sur les produits vendus à l'épicerie.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Épicerie fine située au cœur des Halles/Etienne Marcel dont la spécialité sont les Produits du sud Ouest: foie gras maison, cassoulet, confit de canard, charcuterie maison..ainsi que produits de la mer tel que le saumon fumé, œufs de poisson...
L'épicerie est attenante à un restaurant où vous pouvez déguster tous les classiques faits maison (carpaccio de foie gras cru, escalope de foie gras ou le foie gras mi-cuit) ainsi qu'une carte de saison.
Nous proposons également tous les dimanches du mois de décembre, un Brunch du Terroir .

about_this_biz_business_recommendation.description: Perpétue la tradition littéraire et gourmande du quatier latin en proposant un art de vivre complet.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Yves Camdeborde est un chef cuisinier français né à Pau le 7 décembre 1964. Il est l'un des chefs de file de la cuisine de bistrot. Les journalistes lui portent l'étiquette de chef de la bistronomie.
Il quitte l'école à 14 ans pour devenir apprenti de cuisine. Après avoir obtenu son CAP, il poursuit son apprentissage dans les cuisines du Ritz, du restaurant La Marée, puis de La Tour d'Argent et de l'Hôtel de Crillon.
Il a été formé - entre autres - par Christian Constant
En 1992, il acquiert la Régalade, un restaurant du 14e arrondissement de Paris. En 2005, il rachète un HÔTEL du quartier de l'Odéon et ouvre le Comptoir du Relais Saint-Germain.
Il est depuis 2010 l'un des jurés de l'émission MasterChef. Le 30 novembre, au micro de Sud Radio, on apprend qu'il ne participera pas à la 5e saison de MasterChef.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Un bar à hors d'oeuvre Pas de chaises, pas de tables, juste un zinc où prendre quelques apéritifs concoctés par Yves Camdeborde, avant de rejoindre (ou pas) sa table réservée du Comptoir. Une préface en quelques sortes. Cousin français des sushi bars japonais et des bars à tapas espagnols, l'Avant Comptoir permet de partager un moment de bonne humeur dans un lieu accueillant en dégustant des hors-d'ouvre à l'heure de l'apéritif ou lors d'un repas détendu.

Un thé face aux tuileries La Maison Angelina a été fondée en 1903 et n'a pas tardé à devenir une véritable institution dominicale, un passage obligé pour tout amateur de vrai chocolat et du délicieux Mont-Blanc, l'autre emblème de la maison. L'on retrouve l'enseigne à deux pas des tuileries, dans un décor au style vieille France, où l'on croise aussi bien les familles que les amoureux : une invitation au délice à laquelle peu résistent.

Les meilleurs soufflés de Paris Si la devanture a un petit air ancien, c'est bien parce que le Soufflé, du haut de ses 40 ans, fait aujourd'hui figure de doyen de la rue du Mont Thabor. Son prédécesseur, le Goyesca accueillait déjà des réfugiés Espagnols pendant la guerre civile. Aujourd'hui ce sont des employés de la cour des comptes tout proche qui viennent déguster, dans un cadre confortable, ses soufflés variés salés ou sucrés.

Notre règle d'or : aucun surgelés. Ici, les légumes viennent du marché Saint-Didier et tout est fait maison.
La Coïncidence est un restaurant de cuisine traditionnelle française. Implanté dans le 16ème arrondissement, le commerce se distingue par ses prix abordables, son ambiance détendue et ledynamisme de ses gérants. 

Ancien joueur de golf professionnel, Jean-Baptiste rencontre Alban par hasard lors d'une soirée entre amis, ils décident de s'associer.

Retour vers le 19ème siècle En entrant dans cet établissement, vous aurez immédiatement la sensation de remonter dans le temps (ce qui est normal pour une maison qui existe depuis 1832 et autrefois fréquenté par Sarah Bernhardt !). Cuisine raffinée, service soigné dans une ambiance feutrée et un décor d'antan. On y savoure évidemment plusieurs recettes de nos amis les escargots ainsi que d'autres plats traditionnels. Une carte des vins riche. Le quartier change, pas l'Escargot.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio: Greg : Cuisinier, puis manager, passionné de cuisine et de nature. J’essaie d’allier les deux, de travailler dans le respect de mes convictions . Ben: manager et barman chez Janou, le client est ma priorité .
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Si vous voulez passer un moment de détente en famille ou avec vos amis, vous êtes les bienvenus. Découvrez notre restaurant ouvert 7/7, et goutez à notre cuisine typiquement française. Venez aussi déguster notre carte de vins spécialement élaborée par le patron.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Dans la pure tradition du bistrot Situé dans le quartier Saint-Paul non loin de l'Ile Saint-Louis, le Bistrot le Temps des Cerises vous accueillent dans un esprit 100% bistrot. Dans ce bistrot typique datant de plus de deux siècles, affiches, photos et ardoises affichant les menus donnent au lieu un esprit à la fois traditionnel et convivial. Dans l'assiette, c'est une cuisine française revisitée qui est mise à l'honneur au travers de plats savoureux et inventifs comme le boeuf ficelle et ses légumes en plat principal ou une fricassée de cuisses de grenouilles. La carte change à chaque saison. Le petit zinc convivial accueille également celles et ceux désirant simplement boire un verre.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Ouverte en 1908, trois familles se sont succédées jusqu'aujourd'hui...Les Boudon ont repris la Maison en 1991 et se sont attachés à étoffer la carte des vins et des plats dans la plus grande tradition du Sud Ouest.
Remodelée en 1992 selon les clichés du début du siècle, elle reste fidèle à la tradition des " vieilles " brasseries parisiennes où il fait bon s'attabler. De vieilles familles d'habitués cohabitent avec des convives du monde entier, amoureux de cette ambiance de carte postale .L'appétit doit être solide ...foie gras, confit, cassoulets sont faits maison et rivalisent avec les plus beaux produits en direct de chaque région. On arrose tout cela de petits vins frais, de rosés gouleyants ...ou de grands crus facturés à prix doux. La maison a reçu nombre de convives prestigieux en toute discrétion, ainsi que Mr et Mme Obama en juin 2009. En saison, on peut diner " à la fraîche " sur la terrasse dressée sous les arcades.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Spécialités du Sud-Ouest

On dirait le Sud Dans le quartier du Marais, proche de la place des Vosges, Chez Janou se distingue par sa grande gamme d'apéritifs provençaux. Les pastis y sont particulièrement appréciés et Janou en propose un nombre impressionnant (des dizaines !), un pur moment de bonheur pour les afficionados du Pastaga. La terrasse, très appréciée l'été, est aussi un des points forts de l'établissement. La salade d'épinards au chèvre, la petite friture, le magret de canard au romarin et la crème brûlée à la vanille (ou au pain d'épice) font partie des spécialités de la maison. Ambiance conviviale et simple... comme dans le Sud. Réservation fortement conseillée le soir.

Le dandy Aux abords du Louvre, dans un cadre très chic (éclairage tamisé, vastes baies vitrées, parquet sombre et fauteuils confortables), ce bar-restaurant fait aussi office de bibliothèque où l'on peut emprunter des livres (ou lire la presse) dans l'après-midi. En été, l'agréable terrasse à l'angle de Rivoli permet de siroter un café glacé ou encore goûter la crème catalane au mascarpone agrémentée de dés de mangue. A l'intérieur, l'impression de retourner au XIXème siècle est franchement perceptible. On y retrouve une clientèle cosmopolite et branchée qui semble rentrer en osmose avec les lieux, chic et so british. On aimerait presque un peu plus de calme et de détente dans un lieu aussi cosy. Côté bar, la carte à whisky n'est pas à négliger, loin de là... Une escapade idéale en après-midi, pour un apéritif raffiné ou encore à l'occasion du brunch dominical.

Une table prestigieuse de renommée internationale On ne présente pas l'hôtel Four Seasons George V. Voici son restaurant, dirigé par Eric Briffard qui a pris la suite de Philippe Legendre. Inutile de dire qu'ici la cuisine est élevée au rang d'oeuvre d'art à la croisée de la tradition et de la créativité. Un grand moment de plaisir gastronomique à apprécier dans une superbe cadre alliant classicisme et élégance raffinée avec de grande baies vitrées offrant une vue sur le patio et de très beaux tapis.
menu "retour du marche" entree/plat/fromage/dessert 35 euros

Christine et Fernand Au rez-de-chaussée d'un beau bâtiment en pierres de taille datant du 18è siècle, les trois salles voûtées aux poutres apparentes et aux murs de briquettes rouges de Chez Fernand sont un véritable havre de paix (de fraîcheur en été) et de plaisir pour ceux qui aiment la cuisine traditionnelle française aux accents terroir. Moelleux de chèvre et ricotta au concombre, Os à moelle, pain grillé et gros sel ou Morceau du boucher (poire de bœuf) aux échalotes confites et purée maison, Crème brûlée aux gousses de vanille bourbon.

Dans le coeur du Marais historique Impossible de louper cette adresse : il y a toujours la queue devant! Vous pouvez découvrir les célèbres falafels, contraction de 3 mots qui signifie "fait de plein de miettes"! Pas très engageant à première vue et pourtant! La réputation de la cuisine de ce petit restaurant de cuisine israélienne n'est pas à refaire : ces délicieux pains fourrés de houmous ou de légumes ont trouvé leur public. Idéal pour une pause shopping rapide et à tout petit prix en plus !

L'un des chefs les plus connus, s'habille de rouge et noir Le célèbre chef s'est posé dans le chic 7ème arrondissement, avec un concept original. Un savant mélange d'obscurité et de notes de couleurs rougeoyantes pour l'Atelier de ces messieurs : Joël Robuchon, Axel Manès, Eric Bouchenoire et Philippe Braun. Entre le mobilier de bois noir laqué et le sol en granit sombre, les bocaux d'épices et de légumes jouent la transparence, tandis que les étagères de chrome accrochent l'oeil distrait. Sous les jambons suspendus, costumes et tailleurs chics sont assis sur des tabourets hauts d'un cuir rouge flamboyant disposés tout autour du bar à la japonaise ("teppanyakis"). Ici point de tables, l'heure est à la convivialité et la simplicité, raffinée tout de même. A coté des cultures de bambous et des pyramides d'écrevisses ou de fruits, il reste à commander un homard bleu en salade préparé au moment, un ventrèche de thon à l'huile épicée, des écrevisses à la plancha ou des cannellonis de
The restaurant le volant basque  is a typical French restaurant with a Basque touch and all our products are homemade

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Bob Partrite is the Chief Operating Officer of the Simco Restaurant group on Pier 39. He is passionate about serving fresh sustainable seafood and creating a dining experience that is memorable. His goal is to exceed guests expectations and you will find him in our restaurants on a daily basis. "We are your local PIER 39 restaurant, come visit us and see why".

Warren Simmons was the visionary behind the creation, conceptualizing and development of what would become one of the world's most famous landmarks: PIER 39. Today, over 30 years later, Simco Restaurants continues to own and operate the most successful restaurants on Fisherman's Wharf including the award-winning Pier Market Restaurant, Fog Harbor Fish House, Wipeout Bar & Grill, Eagle Cafe and Biscoff Coffee Corner.
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Fog Harbor Fish House offers the quintessential San Francisco waterfront dining experience. Steeped in tradition, Fog Harbor Fish House was created by the original developers of PIER 39 and is filled with a quarter century of San Francisco history. Family-owned and operated, Fog Harbor Fish House is among the most favored restaurants on the Wharf where we pride ourselves in offering the freshest seafood in San Francisco.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Ranked Top 5 Most Popular Restaurants in SF by Yelp.
Award winning view of the Golden Gate Bridge, and Alcatraz!
Waterfront indoor & outdoor seating. 
First restaurant on Fisherman's Wharf with 100% sustainable seafood.
Fresh fish delivered and hand cut daily.
Fresh sourdough bread baked every 30 minutes.
New England Clam Chowder made from scratch daily.
Vast California wine list and full bar with premium liquor

House of Prime Rib is a San Francisco Landmark.  Our juicy and delicious Prime Rib is made from the highest quality corn-fed beef available.

The House of Prime Rib serves well-marbled Prime Rib in the English Tradition. Our Prime Rib is carved at your table, to your specifications, from our unique stainless steel serving carts. We serve only the best beef available, the top 2% of all beef marketed.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Gayle Pirie and John Clark have been deeply involved in the competitive and innovative ferment of the San Francisco restaurant scene for over two decades. Long standing tenures at Zuni Cafe and Chez Panisse earned them critical approval for the purity, quality and consistency of their cuisine. 

In 2001 the duo took over the kitchen of Foreign Cinema as Chef/Owners and implemented an ever changing Mediterranean influenced menu and full oyster bar, earning the restaurant three stars from the San Francisco Chronicle and ten consecutive "Top 100" rankings. They have also received rave reviews from the New York Times, Gourmet, Cosmopolitan, San Francisco Examiner, SF Weekly, and San Francisco magazine. 

Additionally, Pirie and Clark have published two cookbooks, Country Egg, City Egg in 2000 and reprinted in 2008 by popular demand, and Bride and Groom, published in 2006.

Pirie and Clark live in Berkeley with their two children, Magnus and Pearl.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Foreign Cinema opened in 1999 in San Francisco's Mission District. Offering eclectic California-Mediterranean cuisine, Foreign Cinema's Chefs/Owners Gayle Pirie and John Clark change the menu daily to reflect the finest organic, seasonal produce, meat and fish available.  

Foreign Cinema provides an industrial chic setting with a warm yet lively vibe. The indoor dining room features a fireplace and open kitchen, and foreign and independent films are screened against the white wall in the covered outdoor patio. Adjacent to the restaurant, Laszlo Bar serves as the perfect stop to sip a cocktail after dinner with a bar program paying a playful homage to noteworthy classic and modern films with cocktails such as La Dolce Vita and Vertigo.

about_this_biz_business_recommendation.description: Capo's is our Chicago-style sister restaurant, just 2 blocks away from Tony's Pizza Napoletana. Capo's takes reservations.
Tony's Coal-Fired is our slice house, right next door. If you're in a hurry, or would like a pizza or slice to-go, this is where to go!

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
A small pizzeria in Naples, Italy is the inspiration behind Tony Gemignani's story for Tony's Pizza Napoletana. A fulfillment in his ever growing passion for pizza drew him to self content when he first tried an authentic Neapolitan pizza. Since then he was determined to learn this art of pizza making and one day open a restaurant like no other. Growing up, Tony worked by his mother's side, learning valuable skills he would later implement in operating a successful restaurant. Tony learned the creativity involved in preparing hand crafted dishes, only to include the finest ingredients straight from the heart of Italy.

Since 1991 Tony has been involved in the pizza industry. Since then Tony has won numerous awards including Best Pizza Margherita at the World Pizza Cup in Naples, Italy and Best Pizza Romana at the World Championship of Pizza Makers in 2011. Tony was the first American and non Neapolitan to win this coveted award in Naples. Now right in the heart of North Beach lies Tony
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Tony's Pizza Napoletana is a state of the art full service restaurant that offers several styles of pizzas which include Neapolitan, Classic American and Italian, Sicilian, Pizza Romana, Gluten Free and New York, Detroit and St. Louis Style and displays seven different types of pizza ovens. A delightful array of antipasti, pastas, insalata, and dolci are available at Tony's including a full bar that includes Italian and California wines, aperitifs, digestives and hand crafted artisan cocktails. At Tony's we pride ourselves in using only the finest ingredients which include fresh herbs and honey from our roof-top garden. We import authentic Neapolitan and Italian products each week and support several locally grown organic farmers and artisan cheese makers. All of our purveyors are specifically picked by Tony Gemignani bringing you the highest quality food or drink right to your table.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Tony's Pizza Napoletana is a state of the art full service restaurant that offers several styles of pizzas which include Neapolitan, Classic American and Italian, Sicilian, Pizza Romana, Gluten Free and New York, Detroit and St. Louis Style and displays seven different types of pizza ovens. A delightful array of antipasti, pastas, insalata, and dolci are available at Tony's including a full bar that includes Italian and California wines, aperitifs, digestives and hand crafted artisan cocktails. At Tony's we pride ourselves in using only the finest ingredients which include fresh herbs and honey from our roof-top garden. We import authentic Neapolitan and Italian products each week and support several locally grown organic farmers and artisan cheese makers. All of our purveyors are specifically picked by Tony Gemignani bringing you the highest quality food or drink right to your table.

about_this_biz_business_recommendation.description: Don't forget to visit our second location Larkspur!

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Roma Antica was born in the heart of the Marina District. The product of a rich cultural heritage that passed along for generations, the art of Roman Cuisine, revisited in a modern style.

We aim through our cuisine to share our family tradition, surrounding you with a simple meal in great company. The menu offers a selection of authentic recipes from Rome as well as additional specialties from the magic of sitting around a table, sipping good wine and enjoy all the regions of Italy.

All of this, wrapped in a true Italian accent, will make you feel as if you were living a typical day in Rome, where "the sun kisses you, the wind caresses you and the city protects you!

The partners are Dogukan Solmaz  and Roberto Sbaraglia, a Roman whose father has owned a restaurant in Rome, Antica, for the past 30 years
The two met at hospitality school in Rome in 2005 and have been looking for a place in San Francisco for the past three years.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: The two hope to bring reasonably-priced Italian meals--with an authentic Italian vibe--to the area. And true to the family-friendly spirit of Italian eateries, the restaurant was created with both parents and their children in mind.

about_this_biz_business_recommendation.description: Oyster farm open daily 9-5 w/ retail shellfish sales, picnic tables (by reservation only) and an on site café/oyster bar (open Fri/Sat/Sun/ Mon).
Visit us on your way to wine country!

attributes.about_this_biz_bio: Hi! I'm Ethan, General Manager of Hog Island San Francisco.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Serving sustainably farmed oysters and shellfish raised on our farm on Tomales Bay. Fresh Local Seafood and seafood friendly cocktails featuring small craft spirits and fresh herbs+botanicals.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Rich and Laura were both born and raised in North Beach, San Francisco’s “Little Italy.” Their goal for Sotto Mare is to create a place where friends, neighbors and worldwide visitors can congregate to indulge in the freshest seafood, good wine, and laughter and great stories shared.
The menu was created to be as close to authentic Italian food as possible—cooked just like they do it in Italy. While Sotto Mare is famous for “The Best Damn Crab Cioppino,” it is always testing new dishes and asking customers what new dishes they might enjoy.

attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Specializing in organic wood-fired cuisine, we serve simple food created with seasonal ingredients sourced from local farms and purveyors.

about_this_biz_business_recommendation.description:
Cocktail bar
Serving restrained tiki drinks & bar food which you can create a meal from. 
Great for a date or girls night out. Vinyl DJ Thurs-Sat

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Chef Ravi was born and raised on Oahu in Hawaii. He moved to San Francisco in 1998 to attend The California Culinary Academy. He has worked in many kitchens around the Bay Area and beyond including an 8 year stint at Boulevard working closely with Chef Nancy Oakes where he went on to open Prospect as the executive chef. He left restaurants all together in 2011 after his son Makoa was born. The pop-up: "Liholiho Yacht Club" was born in 2012 as a means to create delicious heritage driven food while still supporting his family and working towards his lifelong dream of having his own restaurant.

In 2014 Ravi joined forces with Jeff Hanak, an owner of Nopa and Nopalito and long time friend. Hanak is a native to SF and brings a solid and local foundation to the LYC team.

Together they strives to create a comfortable environment well balanced and enjoyable. Focusing on Kapur's heritage driven food and Jeff's keen attention to hospitality.
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Back in Hawaii in the early 80's The Kealoha uncles would race Hobie Cats, they threw parties "pop ups" to pay for their supplies. They would go to the beach and throw a party, fire up the grill, ice down the beer, and get a band to play. They would charge a modest price with the intention to make enough money to allow them to do what they loved. They realized they needed a name for their 'organization' and the brothers who lived on Liholiho street decided to name it Liholiho Yacht Club. This is how the modern day LYC was born. We loved the name and the idea: to throw a party to allow you to keep doing what you love.  Grind - Talk Story - Get Jag
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Heritage driven food. 

Cooking and hospitality are the catalyst to gather and enjoy the moment.

Grind - Talk Story - Get Jag
Modern American fine dining in a unique dinner party format

4 stars with over 12K reviews and counting! There's a reason why we're the most Yelped restaurant in the Bay Area and the 6th most Yelped restaurant in the country!  Come on in and try the best New Orleans-inspired brunch, lunch and dinner in the Bay Area!

attributes.about_this_biz_bio: In 1965 when brothers Al Scoma (1920-2007) and his brother Joe heard about a small coffee shop on the Wharf that was for sale, little did they know they were on the road to creating a landmark restaurant. The brothers bought the tiny, six-stool coffee shop on Pier 47 that served local fishermen breakfast and burgers and began the long and ultimately successful process of turning the hidden local hang-out into one of the nation's highest grossing independent restaurants.
attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1965, the Scoma brothers Al and Joe Scoma opened a humble café on the bustling wharf, using their mother's recipes for inspiration. Scoma's own fish receiving station allows public viewing of wild salmon and local Dungeness crab as it's off-loaded from boats and prepared for the kitchen.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Scoma's, located perfectly on the San Francisco Bay, is one of the most iconic restaurants in the city, having opened in 1965.   Since then, the restaurant has provided the freshest, most sustainable and delicious local seafood to locals and visitors alike.  Priding itself on its "Pier To Plate" menu,  Scoma's owners, chefs and management pride themselves on their deep relationships with the local fishing community where they source most of their seafood.  Guests can even watch the fishing boats pull up to the restaurant's own fish receiving station and get a glimpse of that day's catch before it is artfully served on their plate.  Some classic favorites include the "Lazy Man's" Cioppino, Fresh Dungeness Crab, World Famous Clam Chowder, Prawns Annuzzi, and a wide variety of pastas and seasonal selections.

Scoma's also offers a full bar with a fantastic craft cocktail program and an extensive local beer, award-winning wine list for those looking to relax and imbibe while watching the sun set over the water.

Scoma's offers complimentary valet parking, just right in front of our restaurant. 

Please call us if you need any assistance with directions or anything else.  We hope to see you at Scoma's soon!

attributes.about_this_biz_bio: Bob cannot wait for your visit!
attributes.about_this_biz_history: We've been around for over two decades and we can't wait for you to come in and dine with us!  Find us with a near me search.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Crab House is well-known for its world-famous "Killer Crab®" (2lb+ whole Dungeness Crab roasted in a secret garlic sauce served on a sizzling iron skillet) as well as favorites like shrimp & mussel skillets, garlic noodles, crab fried rice and crab chowder. If you love crab, this is THE place. 

Guests rave about the cozy circular firepit, upbeat music, the sound of sizzling skillets, and an irresistible garlic aroma throughout the dining room. Hot skillets keep crustaceans warm as you crack open and devour tender meaty bites - but you'll depart clean thanks to complimentary bibs and moist towelettes. This lively cozy restaurant is ideal for date night, friends night out or family gathering. 

Located upstairs on PIER 39, tucked away from the crowds, the dining room featuring breath-taking views of the Golden Gate Bridge, Alcatraz and Fisherman's Wharf.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: Opened in June 2010 in the heart of San Francisco's Financial District.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Chef Tyler Florence's flagship restaurant is a timeless San Francisco tavern featuring authentic American dishes inspired by local cuisine at the turn of the 20th century. Ranging from classic comforts to rustic delicacies, the menu also features California wines by the bottle, quality draft beers, organic draft root beer and classic Victorian-era cocktails. 

If you have insights into your dining experience and how it fell short of expectations we ask that you please reach out to us directly.  Negative reviews have a significant impact on our business, often more than people realize when leaving them. We always welcome feedback and aim to rectify any shortcomings whenever possible.
